in <PERSON>Callan</PERSON>'s of Fownes's Street; but, as the retort was after the manner
of the liberal shepherds in the eclogues, he had to admit that it was
not as clever as <PERSON>Farrington</PERSON>'s retort. At this <PERSON>Farrington</PERSON> told the boys
