drops of liquor from his moustache with the aid of his lower lip.

When that round was over there was a pause. <PERSON>O'Halloran</PERSON> had money but
neither of the other two seemed to have any; so the whole party left
the shop somewhat regretfully. At the corner of Duke Street <PERSON>Higgins</PERSON> and
<PERSON>Nosey Flynn</PERSON> bevelled off to the left while the other three turned back
